          "kind": "thinking",
          "value": "The error is: `SyntaxError: Unexpected token 'export'` at `loadESMFromCJS`. This means the built main process JS file is trying to `require()` an ESM module (one of our packages that uses `export` statements). \n\nThe issue: electron-vite bundles the main process to CJS (CommonJS), but our workspace packages export ESM syntax. The `externalizeDepsPlugin()` in electron-vite externalizes node_modules packages, but our workspace packages (linked via `workspace:*`) are resolved to their source `.ts` files and the bundler tries to include them as CJS — but they contain `export` statements.\n\nWait, looking more carefully: the error says `loadESMFromCJS` — it's trying to load an ESM module from a CJS context. The built `out/main/index.js` is CJS, and it tries to `require()` or `import` one of our packages. If the package's package.json doesn't have `\"type\": \"module\"`, Node treats `.js` as CJS. But if the package has `\"type\": \"module\"` in its package.json, Node treats all `.js` as ESM.\n\nWait, actually the issue might be different. Let me think...\n\nelectron-vite builds the main process as SSR (CJS). The `externalizeDepsPlugin()` externalizes dependencies listed in package.json, so they're loaded via `require()` at runtime. But our workspace packages:\n- Have `\"main\": \"./src/index.ts\"` — pointing to TypeScript sources\n- Node.js can't load `.ts` files\n\nThe electron-vite plugin handles this for static imports by bundling them. But after bundling, the output `out/main/index.js` might still be trying to load external packages that weren't properly bundled.\n\nActually, the real issue: the static imports from workspace packages are being bundled INLINE (not externalized) because they're workspace packages. When bundled, the ESM `export` statements are converted to CJS by Vite. But something is going wrong — maybe one of the transitive dependencies is causing issues.\n\nLet me check what's in the built `out/main/index.js` to see what's happening.\n\nActually, looking at the build output: `out/main/index.js  8.03 kB` — that's very small. It means most of the dependencies ARE being externalized (not bundled). The workspace packages are being treated as external.\n\nThe fix: I need to tell electron-vite NOT to externalize our workspace packages. They should be bundled into the main process output.\n\nLet me read the electron.vite.config.ts.",
